						<summary>

						<p>The date is given as Vibhava (?), Kumbha, śu. 10, Monday, Punarvasu (=A.D. 1290, February 20). The cyclic year was Virōdhi.</p>						

						<p>This seems to record a gift of money with the interest on which offerings and worship were to be conducted in the temple on a specific day of the year on the occasion of a <hi rend="italic">yāga</hi> in honour of god Vishvaksēna by the <hi rend="italic">[Darma]talattār</hi> with whom the amount was deposited by the donor one [Ār]yaputra, grandson of Kiḍāmbi Rāmadāsa.</p>						

						</summary>
